contentrichtext.text: <!-------------------------------------------------------------------------------> <!-- MoS:Disambiguation - prefer ONE LINK per entry, short descriptions. --> <!-- Avoid piping, external links, and red links with little article potential --> <!-------------------------------------------------------------------------------> {{wiktionary|Browning|browned|browning}} '''Browning''' may refer to: {{tocright}} ==Places== * [[Browning, Illinois]], USA * [[Browning, Montana]], USA * [[Browning, Wisconsin]], USA * [[Browning, Missouri]], USA <!--* [[Browning Hill]], in [[Brown County, Indiana]]; sometimes called Browning Mountain --> * [[Browning, Saskatchewan]], Canada * [[Browning No. 34, Saskatchewan]], Canada; rural municipality ==People== * [[Browning (name)]] ==Other== * [[Browning (food process)]], the chemical process of browning food * [[Browning (partial cooking)]], the cooking process that removes excessive fat from meat and changes its color to a light brown * [[Gravy| Gravy browning]], a substance used to darken and flavour gravies, soups etc * Browning, a [[Jamaican Patois]] term for a light skinned person of African or East Indian descent * [[Browning (steel)]], a surface finishing process to increase corrosion resistance * A [[John Browning#Products|series of firearms]] by inventor John Browning ** [[Browning machine gun (disambiguation)]], several machine guns designed by John Browning * [[Browning Arms Company]], initially marketing the sporting designs of John Browning ** [[Browning BDM]], a semi-automatic pistol developed in the 1990s * {{MV|Browning}}, a coaster * [[Browning Mummery (Electronic sound works)]] (1983), by the Australian musician Andrew Lonsdale (1961â€“) ==See also== * {{Intitle|Browning}} {{disambiguation|geo}}
